      • getVariableNode

        public TreeNode getVariableNode()
        Get the node that stores the variable that is having its value assigned. In other words, the left hand value of the equation. For instance, in the statement: "int j = 35" int j is the left hand value of the equation.

        This does not return a VariableNode type because an ArrayAccessNode is also a valid left hand value to an equation.
        Returns:
        The TreeNode that holds the value of the variable that is to be assigned.

      • decodeStatement

        public static AssignmentNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                             java.lang.String statement,
                             Location location)
        Decode the given statement into an AssignmentNode if possible. If it is not possible, then null is returned.

        Example inputs include:
        • int variableName = 45
        • personsName = "Bob"
        • Person myPeep = new Person(54)
        • area = width * height / 2
        • int newSize = array.getSize() + 5
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent of the current statement.
        statement - The statement to decode into an AssignmentNode.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        Returns:
        The new AssignmentNode if it decodes properly. If not, it returns null.

      • decodeStatement

        public static AssignmentNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                             java.lang.String statement,
                             Location location,
                             boolean addDeclaration)
        Decode the given statement into an AssignmentNode if possible. If it is not possible, then null is returned.

        Example inputs include:
        • int variableName = 45
        • personsName = "Bob"
        • Person myPeep = new Person(54)
        • area = width * height / 2
        • int newSize = array.getSize() + 5
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent of the current statement.
        statement - The statement to decode into an AssignmentNode.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        addDeclaration - Whether or not to add the declaration to the nearest scope, if the left hand value of the equation is a variable declaration.
        Returns:
        The new AssignmentNode if it decodes properly. If not, it returns null.
